    "reasoning": "The computer was on for 100 hours. To find h, the remainder when dividing 100 by 24 (hours in a day), we compute 100 \u00f7 24 = 4 remainder 4, so h = 4. Then k = h + 7 = 4 + 7 = 11. We need three distinct numbers from the list {2, 3, 4, 6} that sum to 11. Checking all combinations: (2,3,4) sums to 9, (2,3,6) sums to 11, (2,4,6) sums to 12, (3,4,6) sums to 13. The only triple that sums to 11 is (2,3,6). Their product is 2 \u00d7 3 \u00d7 6 = 36.",
